article.headline: E. Illinois 57, Ind.-South Bend 40
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Levi Noel and Shaun Pratl scored 10 points each as Eastern Illinois topped Indiana-South Bend 57-40 on Saturday night. James Hallowell and Tyler Laser added eight points apiece for the Panthers (1-3). Kyle Heatherly had 14 points and Jake Berger added 10 for Indiana-South Bend, an NAIA school that designated the game as an exhibition. The Titans' season record remains 2-5. The Panthers limited Indiana-South Bend to 36.4-percent (12 of 33) shooting and forced 20 turnovers.
